[The above news items represent the current state of alertness and fears in
vast parts of Asia. Hopefully, in case of suspected HPAI spread to hitherto
unaffected countries, veterinary investigations and subsequent laboratory
tests will be carried out at an early stage. Transparency should be
significantly improved compared to that recently experienced in several of
the countries affected in Eastern Asia.
India's information to the OIE indicates status 0000, meaning "disease
never reported". According to the last update of OIE's Handistatus
database, the last monthly Indian report, indicating "no case", related to
October 2003. - Mod.AS]
